1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
StellarFund — cross-border crowdfunding on Stellar.

2
00:00:05,000 --> 00:00:11,000
Someone in Germany can fund a bakery in Kenya in seconds, for cents.

3
00:00:11,000 --> 00:00:17,000
Funds sit in a smart contract and release as milestones are met.

4
00:00:17,000 --> 00:00:24,000
Discovery: search and category filters; campaigns have titles, images and categories.

5
00:00:24,000 --> 00:00:30,000
Active and past campaigns are separated for clarity.

6
00:00:30,000 --> 00:00:36,000
Onboarding is one tap: Connect a wallet…

7
00:00:36,000 --> 00:00:44,000
…then "Get Test USDC" — it funds the account, sets the USDC trustline and mints 500 test USDC.

8
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:52,000
Create a campaign with a title, description, category, cover image and milestones.

9
00:00:52,000 --> 00:00:58,000
The campaign is deployed on-chain; its identity is saved off-chain.

10
00:00:58,000 --> 00:01:06,000
Open a campaign and see the milestone timeline.

11
00:01:06,000 --> 00:01:14,000
Contribute in USDC — a real, wallet-signed transaction. Contributions are capped at the goal.

12
00:01:14,000 --> 00:01:22,000
The Proof board lists every unique backer wallet, with links to stellar.expert.

13
00:01:22,000 --> 00:01:30,000
Every interaction is permanent and publicly verifiable on Stellar Testnet.

14
00:01:30,000 --> 00:01:38,000
When a milestone is approved, the creator releases that tranche of funds.

15
00:01:38,000 --> 00:01:46,000
The fiat ramp runs the real SEP-10 and SEP-24 protocol against a Stellar test anchor.

16
00:01:46,000 --> 00:01:53,000
Pay fiat, receive USDC — and back to fiat on withdrawal. No real money; testnet only.

17
00:01:53,000 --> 00:02:01,000
A private analytics dashboard shows live, on-chain stats by category and top campaigns.

18
00:02:01,000 --> 00:02:09,000
Architecture: a Factory deploys each Escrow, which records success in a Reputation contract.

19
00:02:09,000 --> 00:02:16,000
Six wallets plus WalletConnect, English and Turkish, analytics, and a PWA.

20
00:02:16,000 --> 00:02:24,000
Next: creator profiles, comments and updates, notifications, and a path to mainnet.

21
00:02:24,000 --> 00:02:30,000
StellarFund — fund anyone, anywhere.
